      'Block $A$ of mass $m_A=3.0$ kg rests above the flat horizontal surface of block $B$ of mass $m_B=6.0$ kg, which in turn rests on a smooth horizontal surface as shown.\n![SkillUpp Image](https://assets.revisionvillage.com/public/question/916d5984-df39-4104-8ae4-f0b1bc8e95d8/images/95a83caf-67bf-4f98-b1f3-d2746f45ddb2/Screensh0ot%202025-05-27%20at%201.33.09%E2%80%AFPM.JPEG)\n\n\nThe coefficients of static and kinetic friction between $A$ and $B$ are $\\mu_s=0.2$ and $\\mu_k=0.1$ respectively. A horizontal force of $F=7.0$ N is applied towards the right on block $A$. Assuming acceleration due to gravity $g \\approx 10$ m s$^{-2}$, the direction and magnitude of acceleration $a_B$ of block $B$ are:\n\n$\\hspace{1em}$ Direction of $\\bf{a_B}$ $\\hspace{1em}$ $\\hspace{1em}$ Magnitude of $\\bf{a_B}$ $\\hspace{1em}$ $\\hspace{1.5em}$A.$\\hspace{1.5em}$To the left$1.0$ m s$^{-2}$ $\\hspace{1.5em}$B.$\\hspace{1.5em}$To the left$0.5$ m s$^{-2}$ $\\hspace{1.5em}$C.$\\hspace{1.5em}$To the right$1.0$ m s$^{-2}$ $\\hspace{1.5em}$D.$\\hspace{1.5em}$To the right$0.5$ m s$^{-2}$',
