      'A bullet of mass $m$ is fired horizontally at a speed $v$ into a block of mass $M$. The bullet remains inside the block upon collision. The block is connected to a light inextensible string so that the collision of the bullet causes the block to move from position 1 to a maximum height at position 2 as shown in the diagram.\n![SkillUpp Image](https://assets.revisionvillage.com/public/question/61bc0b12-8828-424b-bc0f-78b36fb6313d/images/abad9cd7-7f2a-4a42-a4c2-87c5213fdda8/image.png)\n\n\nIf air resistance is negligible, which of the following expressions is gives the value of $h$, the vertical distance moved by the center of mass?\n\n\n\n- A. $\\hspace{1em}  $ $\\dfrac{mv^2}{2gM}$\n- B. $\\hspace{1em}  $ $\\dfrac{m^2v^2}{2gM^2}$\n- C. $\\hspace{1em}  $ $\\dfrac{mv^2}{2g(m+M)}$\n- D. $\\hspace{1em}  $ $\\dfrac{m^2v^2}{2g(m+M)^2}$\n',
